The paper proposes a novel network architecture for vessel segmentation in fundus images, which is a common task in ophthalmology. The approach involves using a hierarchical model to stratify ground-truth masks into different thickness levels, and a two-stream adversarial network with a balanced loss function and integration operation. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category, as it deals with image analysis and segmentation. Additionally, the use of a neural network and loss function indicates that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of fundus images suggests that it may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category, and the use of an adversarial network suggests that it may also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
